From 00343ff3b2d7104afa2c7273e7362588742f19c8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 11:03:39 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] feat(test-plan): add scenario-plan render template (#272)

Add a fourth scenario-plan body template to the pure render layer, reproducing the hand-authored exemplar shape: optional intro then per-scenario blocks (Preconditions / numbered Steps / Expected / a pass marker or a blocked-or-omitted note / captioned inline screenshots, or a contract-check block for the non-screenshot modality), horizontal-rule separators, and an Environment footer.

Purely additive behaviour: registers scenario-plan in KNOWN_TEMPLATES and dispatches to a new render_scenario_plan. The scenario shape (Scenario / ScenarioImage / ScenarioSection TypedDicts, coerce, render) lives in a new _test_plan_scenario module; TestPlanState composes ScenarioSection and round-trips the new keys via coerce_state. The three existing templates are unchanged in behaviour. BLUEPRINT updated to document the fourth template.

To keep each module under the module-health cap, the two non-default workflow renderers (browser-click-first, link-api) move verbatim into a new _test_plan_workflow_templates module, reusing the render layer's workflow-enumeration and how-to-test helpers via injected callables (one-directional dependency). 105 tests in test_post_test_plan pass, proving the relocated templates are behaviour-identical.
